Project name- Elevating Risk Assessment
Domain-finance
Client name- QBE Insurance Group
Tools- ML Models, Jupyter, Anaconda, Power bi, MySQL,python.
Package- scikit-Learn,Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib and seaborn,TensorFlow.
Problem Statement:
The primary objective of this project is to develop advanced risk assessment models using data science methodologies to improve the accuracy and effectiveness of risk evaluation in the shipping insurance industry.
The project will address the following key aspects.
Project Overview:
The goal of this project is to develop predictive models that assess the risk associated with different shipments in the shipping insurance industry.
These models will take into account various factors such as vessel age, cargo type, route hazards, and weather conditions to identify high-risk shipments.
Machine learning algorithms will be employed for this purpose.

Data Collection:

Data Sources: Gather historical data on shipping accidents, vessel characteristics, cargo types, route information, and weather conditions.
You may obtain this data from industry databases, government agencies, satellite data providers, and insurance company records.

Data Preprocessing:
Clean and preprocess the data, including handling missing values, outliers, and data normalization. Prepare the dataset for model training.

Feature Engineering:
3. Feature Selection:
Identify relevant features that impact shipping risk.
These can include vessel age, cargo value, cargo type, past accident history, and weather conditions during the voyage.

Feature Engineering:
Create new features if necessary, such as aggregations, interactions, or transformations that may enhance the predictive power of the model.
Model Building:
5. Algorithm Selection: Choose appropriate machine learning algorithms for risk assessment.
Common choices include logistic regression, decision trees, random forests, gradient boosting, and neural networks.

Model Training:
Split the dataset into training and validation sets.
Train the models using historical data, where the target variable is a binary indicator of whether a shipment resulted in a loss or not.

Hyper parameter Tuning:
Optimize model hyper parameters to achieve the best performance.
Techniques like grid search or random search can be used.

Model Evaluation:
8. Model Evaluation Metrics:
Assess model performance using metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and ROC AUC. 
Determine the model's ability to correctly classify high-risk shipments.

Interpretability and Explainability:
9. Model Interpretation:
Ensure the models are interpretable, especially in an insurance context where explanations for risk assessments are crucial.
Utilize techniques like SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) values or LIME (Local Interpretable Model-agnostic Explanations) for model interpretability.

Validation and Deployment:
10. Validation:
Validate the model's performance on unseen data to ensure it generalizes well.
